{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-6009].
  {panel}

The POP boxes Jira reads get slowly cluttered with email that's not read in by Jira. This includes email from non-accepted email addresses and accidentally sent email. Each time jira reads through the email box, all email is scanned and for example emails from users on issues where they have no right to post result in long error log messages.

This is causing a huge amount of excess error logging in our Jira and is forcing our administrative staff to continuously manually clean up the boxes.

Could you please add a feature for Jira to purge any email boxes from the email it's been unable to read/import?

If, for any reason, Jira fails to send the email (e.g. the mail server rejects it because of security policy) then the mail seems to get stuck in the send queue. It doesnt ever get moved to the error queue...

I dont think this is a recent thing - the same problem existed in 2.5.3...

Looking at the code, I can see what the bug is:

if (item.getSendCount() > 10)
    errorItems.add(item);
else
    failed.add(item);

... later ...

items.addAll(failed);

However every concrete implementation of item.getSendCount() overrides the AbstractMailQueueItem implementation and returns 0

    public int getSendCount()
    {
        return 0;
    }


D'oh!

